{
  "texts": [
    "YOLO enhances object recognition by combining high-level feature mapping with a reliable evaluation of various item categories, resulting in precise predictions represented in bounding boxes, as shown in Figure 6a.",
    "This innovative design, shown in Figure 6b, divides the input image into SxS cells using a grid-based method, with each cell providing bounding box features and essential confidence scores.",
    "The probability of an object's presence and the accuracy of the bounding box location are carefully combined to yield the confidence score.",
    "Pr (project)=1 indicates the target object's presence, while Pr(object)=0 indicates its absence.",
    "YOLO ensures substantial accuracy in object localization evaluations using the Intersection over Union (IoU) metric, a crucial measure of alignment between the actual and predicted boxes."
  ]
}